7</b>  <a class="mw-selflink selflink">Globalization</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:History" title="Portal:History">History</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Human_rights" title="Portal:Human rights">Human rights</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Internet" title="Portal:Internet">Internet</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Law" title="Portal:Law">Law</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Philosophy" title="Portal:Philosophy">Philosophy</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Social_movements" title="Portal:Social movements">Social movements</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Social_sciences" title="Portal:Social sciences">Social sciences</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Social_welfare_and_social_work" title="Portal:Social welfare and social work">Social welfare and social work</a>&#160;<b>\xc2\xb7</b>  <a href="/wiki/Portal:Sociology" title="Portal:Sociology">Sociology</a></p>\n</div>\n<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0px" style="font-size:100%">\n<tr style="font-size:200%; font-family:Arial; color:white; letter-spacing:.3em;background:#08088A;">\n<td align="center" height="100px">\n<p><span><b>The Globalization Portal</b></span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" valign="top" style="background:transparent;">\n<table width="100%" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="6" style="background:blue; border-style:solid; border-width:1px; border-color:white;">\n<tr>\n<td width="55%" valign="top" style="padding: 0; margin:0;">\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Introduction">Introduction</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table class="vertical-navbox nowraplinks hlist" style="float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%;width:18.0em;">\n<tr>\n<th style="padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em"><a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">Globalization</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0.2em 0 0.4em"><a href="/wiki/File:WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg" class="image"><img alt="WikiProject Globalization Logo.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg/100px-WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg/150px-WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg/200px-WikiProject_Globalization_Logo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="900" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Outline_of_globalization" title="Outline of globalization">Outline</a></li>\n<li><a class="mw-selflink selflink">Portal</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Global_studies" title="Global studies">Studies</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization">Project</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Dimensions_of_globalization" title="Dimensions of globalization">Dimensions</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class="hlist" style="padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Category:Globalization" title="Category:Globalization">Category</a></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Globalization_sidebar" title="Template:Globalization sidebar"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Globalization_sidebar" title="Template talk:Globalization sidebar"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Globalization_sidebar&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">Globalization</a></b> (or <b>globalisation</b>\xe2\x80\x94see <a href="/wiki/American_and_British_English_spelling_differences#-ise.2C_-ize_.28-isation.2C_-ization.29" title="American and British English spelling differences">spelling differences</a>) is the process of international integration arising from the interchange of <a href="/wiki/World_view" title="World view">world views</a>, products, ideas, and other aspects of <a href="/wiki/Culture" title="Culture">culture</a>. Put in simple terms, globalization refers to processes that increase world-wide exchanges of national and cultural resources. Advances in <a href="/wiki/Transportation" class="mw-redirect" title="Transportation">transportation</a> and <a href="/wiki/Telecommunication" title="Telecommunication">telecommunications</a> infrastructure, including the rise of the <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a>, are major factors in globalization, generating further <a href="/wiki/Interdependence" title="Interdependence">interdependence</a> of economic and cultural activities.</p>\n<div role="note" class="shortcutbox shortcutbox-left plainlist noprint" style="float: left; border: 1px solid #aaa; background: #fff; margin: .3em 1em .3em .3em; padding: 8px 6px; text-align: center; font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold;"><span id="P:GLBZ"></span><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut" title="Wikipedia:Shortcut">Shortcut</a>:\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=P:GLBZ&amp;redirect=no">P:GLBZ</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The term Globalization can also be referred to as the process of opening up all national economies in a globalized market. Globalization is mainly used in the economic field, but it affects all human activities: industry, services, trade, politics, social, culture, religion, transport, health ... It also concerns communication and exchanges between the entire world and different cultures so that we would all become a "global village." However, this would be very difficult to operate in a purely national market because the countries that already have a stable economic system, would not accept to make a change on their economic system. Also, very conservative countries would never want anything to change in their culture.</p>\n<p>Humans have interacted over long distances for thousands of years. The overland <a href="/wiki/Silk_Road" title="Silk Road">Silk Road</a> that connected <a href="/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Africa" title="Africa">Africa</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> is a good example of the transformative power of translocal exchange that existed in the "<a href="/wiki/Old_World" title="Old World">Old World</a>". Philosophy, religion, language, the arts, and other aspects of culture spread and mixed as nations exchanged products and ideas. In the 15th and 16th centuries, Europeans made important discoveries in their exploration of the oceans, including the start of transatlantic travel to the "<a href="/wiki/New_World" title="New World">New World</a>" of the <a href="/wiki/Americas" title="Americas">Americas</a>. Global movement of people, goods, and ideas expanded significantly in the following centuries. Early in the 19th century, the development of new forms of transportation (such as the <a href="/wiki/Steamship" title="Steamship">steamship</a> and <a href="/wiki/Railroads" class="mw-redirect" title="Railroads">railroads</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Telecommunication" title="Telecommunication">telecommunications</a> that "compressed" time and space allowed for increasingly rapid rates of global interchange. In the 20th century, <a href="/wiki/Road_vehicle" class="mw-redirect" title="Road vehicle">road vehicles</a>, <a href="/wiki/Intermodal_freight_transport" title="Intermodal freight transport">intermodal transport</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Airline" title="Airline">airlines</a> made transportation even faster. The advent of electronic communications, most notably <a href="/wiki/Mobile_phones" class="mw-redirect" title="Mobile phones">mobile phones</a> and <a href="/wiki/The_Internet" class="mw-redirect" title="The Internet">the Internet</a>, connected billions of people in new ways by the beginning of the 21st century.</p>\n<p>The term globalization has been in increasing use since the mid-1980s and especially since the mid-1990s. In 2000, the <a href="/wiki/International_Monetary_Fund" title="International Monetary Fund">International Monetary Fund</a> (IMF) identified four basic aspects of globalization: <a href="/wiki/Trade" title="Trade">trade</a> and <a href="/wiki/Financial_transaction" title="Financial transaction">transactions</a>, <a href="/wiki/Capital_(economics)" title="Capital (economics)">capital</a> and <a href="/wiki/Investment" title="Investment">investment</a> movements, <a href="/wiki/Human_migration" title="Human migration">migration</a> and movement of people, and the dissemination of <a href="/wiki/Knowledge" title="Knowledge">knowledge</a>. Further, environmental challenges such as <a href="/wiki/Climate_change" title="Climate change">climate change</a>, cross-boundary water and air <a href="/wiki/Pollution" title="Pollution">pollution</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Over-fishing" class="mw-redirect" title="Over-fishing">over-fishing</a> of the ocean are linked with globalization. Globalizing processes affect and are affected by <a href="/wiki/Business" title="Business">business</a> and <a href="/wiki/Labor_(economics)" class="mw-redirect" title="Labor (economics)">work</a> organization, <a href="/wiki/Economics" title="Economics">economics</a>, <a href="/wiki/Society" title="Society">socio</a>-<a href="/wiki/Cultural" class="mw-redirect" title="Cultural">cultural</a> resources, and the <a href="/wiki/Natural_environment" title="Natural environment">natural environment</a>.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center; margin:0.25em auto 0.75em"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><span style="color:aqua"><b>View new selections below</b> (purge)</span></span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Selected_person/2&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_person">Selected person</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table style="background: transparent;">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="float:left;margin-right:8px;"><a href="/wiki/File:ArjunAppadurai.jpg" class="image" title="Arjun Appadurai during a Q-A session at York University\'s 50-50 Symposium in Toronto, Canada (2009)"><img alt="Arjun Appadurai during a Q-A session at York University\'s 50-50 Symposium in Toronto, Canada (2009)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/ArjunAppadurai.jpg/250px-ArjunAppadurai.jpg" width="250" height="227" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/ArjunAppadurai.jpg/375px-ArjunAppadurai.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/ArjunAppadurai.jpg/500px-ArjunAppadurai.jpg 2x" data-file-width="720" data-file-height="654" /></a></div>\n<b>Arjun Appadurai<br /></b> <abbr title="Born">B.</abbr>&#160;1949<br />\n<br />\n<b><a href="/wiki/Arjun_Appadurai" title="Arjun Appadurai">Arjun Appadurai</a></b> was born in <a href="/wiki/Mumbai" title="Mumbai">Mumbai</a> (Bombay), <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a> and educated in <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a> before going to the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>. He graduated from <a href="/wiki/St._Xavier%27s_High_School,_Fort" title="St. Xavier\'s High School, Fort">St. Xavier\'s High School, Fort</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mumbai" title="Mumbai">Mumbai</a>, and earned his Intermediate Arts degree from <a href="/wiki/Elphinstone_College" title="Elphinstone College">Elphinstone College</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mumbai" title="Mumbai">Mumbai</a>, before coming to the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>. He then received his B.A. from <a href="/wiki/Brandeis_University" title="Brandeis University">Brandeis University</a> in 1970. His doctoral work was based on the car festival held in the Parthasarathi temple in <a href="/wiki/Triplicane" title="Triplicane">Triplicane</a>, <a href="/wiki/Madras" class="mw-redirect" title="Madras">Madras</a>. In his anthropological work, he discusses the importance of the <a href="/wiki/Modernity" title="Modernity">modernity</a> of nation states and <a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">globalization</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="float: left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Globalization/Selected_person" title="Portal:Globalization/Selected person">More selected biographies\xe2\x80\xa6</a></b></div>\n<div style="float: right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Arjun_Appadurai" title="Arjun Appadurai">Read more\xe2\x80\xa6</a></b></div>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Selected_picture/2&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture">Selected picture</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="text-align: center;">\n<div style="display:table; margin: 0 auto 5px auto; padding:7px; border:4px ridge">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png" class="image" title="1901 chart of undersea telegraph cabling"><img alt="1901 chart of undersea telegraph cabling" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png/400px-1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png" width="400" height="324" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png/600px-1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png/800px-1901_Eastern_Telegraph_cables.png 2x" data-file-width="1800" data-file-height="1458" /></a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="noprint" style="display:table; margin: 0 auto; width:33%;"></div>\n<p>Eastern Telegraph Company 1901 chart of undersea <b><a href="/wiki/Telegraph" class="mw-redirect" title="Telegraph">telegraph</a></b> cabling. An example of modern globalizing <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a> in the beginning of the 20th century.</p>\n</div>\n<div class="noprint" style="border:0; padding:0; margin:0;"><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:left; width:32%;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Globalization/Selected_picture" title="Portal:Globalization/Selected picture">More selected pictures...</a></b></span><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:center; width:34%;">&#160;</span><span style="display:inline-block; text-align:right; width:32%;"><b><a href="/wiki/Telegraph" class="mw-redirect" title="Telegraph">Read more...</a></b></span></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-right">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Selected_article/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article">Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table style="background: transparent;">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:8px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif" class="image" title="Of the factors influencing the duration of economic growth in both developed and developing countries, income equality has a more beneficial impact than trade openness, sound political institutions, and foreign investment."><img alt="Of the factors influencing the duration of economic growth in both developed and developing countries, income equality has a more beneficial impact than trade openness, sound political institutions, and foreign investment." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif/250px-Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif" width="250" height="135" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif/375px-Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif/500px-Berg_Ostry_2011_Chart_4.gif 2x" data-file-width="978" data-file-height="528" /></a></div>\n<b><a href="/wiki/Economic_globalization" title="Economic globalization">Economic globalization</a></b> is the increasing economic interdependence of national economies across the world through a rapid increase in <a href="/wiki/Cross-border" class="mw-redirect" title="Cross-border">cross-border</a> movement of goods, service, technology, and capital. Whereas <a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">globalization</a> is centered around the rapid development of science and technology and increasing cross-border division of labor, economic globalization is propelled by the rapid growing significance of information in all types of productive activities and marketization, and the advance of science and technologies. Depending on the paradigm, economic globalization can be viewed as either a positive or a negative phenomenon.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="float: left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Globalization/Selected_article" title="Portal:Globalization/Selected article">More selected articles...</a></b></div>\n<div style="float: right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Economic_globalization" title="Economic globalization">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<p><br /></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Tasks&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Things_you_can_do">Things you can do</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b>Want to help?</b></p>\n<div style="float:right">\n<p><span class="editlink noprint plainlinks navbar"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization/to_do&amp;action=edit">edit</a></span></p>\n</div>\n<p><br /></p>\n<p>This is WikiProject Globalization\'s <b>to do</b> page.</p>\n<table style="background:none;width:auto;">\n<tr>\n<td style="vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg/50px-Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg.png" width="50" height="50" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg/75px-Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg/100px-Nuvola_apps_korganizer.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /></a><br />\n<div style="width: 55px; height: 0px;"></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="position: relative; left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; z-index: 15;">Here are some <b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Community_portal/Opentask" title="Wikipedia:Community portal/Opentask">tasks awaiting attention</a>:</b>\n<ul style="font-size: 100%; margin: 0px; padding: 0.3em 0px 0.3em 25px;">\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Requested_articles" title="Wikipedia:Requested articles">Article requests</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <a href="/w/index.php?title=Global_risk_society&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Global risk society (page does not exist)">Global risk society</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Global_flows&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Global flows (page does not exist)">Global flows</a> - <b>see</b> <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization/Requested_articles" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization/Requested articles">Full list of requested articles</a></li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Version_1.0_Editorial_Team/Assessment" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Version 1.0 Editorial Team/Assessment">Assess</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <a href="/wiki/Category:Unassessed_Globalization_articles" title="Category:Unassessed Globalization articles">Unassessed Globalization articles</a> (20) and <a href="/wiki/Category:Unknown-importance_Globalization_articles" title="Category:Unknown-importance Globalization articles">Unknown-importance Globalization articles</a> (37).</li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Categorization" title="Wikipedia:Categorization">Categorization</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <b>Place</b> <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:WikiProject_Globalization" title="Template:WikiProject Globalization">WikiProject Globalization</a>|class=category}}</code> on the talkpages of sub-categories in <a href="/wiki/Category:Globalization" title="Category:Globalization">Category:Globalization</a>.</li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Cleanup" title="Wikipedia:Cleanup">Cleanup</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <a href="/wiki/Category:Globalization_articles_needing_attention" title="Category:Globalization articles needing attention">Globalization articles needing attention</a> (2). <a class="external text" href="https://tools.wmflabs.org/bambots/cwb/alpha/Globalization.html">As of May 10, 2016, of the 411 articles in this project 252 or 61% are marked for cleanup, with 731 issues in total.</a></li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Writing_better_articles" title="Wikipedia:Writing better articles">Expand</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <b>bring</b> <a href="/wiki/Globalization" title="Globalization">Globalization</a> up to GA status; expand: <a href="/wiki/Outline_of_globalization" title="Outline of globalization">Outline of globalization</a>, <a href="/wiki/Criticisms_of_globalization" title="Criticisms of globalization">Criticisms of globalization</a>, <a href="/wiki/Globalization_in_China" title="Globalization in China">Globalization in China</a>; see also this <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization/Main_articles" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization/Main articles">WikiProject\'s Main articles</a>.</li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(infoboxes)" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (infoboxes)">Infobox</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <a href="/wiki/Category:Globalization_articles_needing_infoboxes" title="Category:Globalization articles needing infoboxes">Globalization articles needing infoboxes</a> (6).</li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub" title="Wikipedia:Stub">Stubs</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <b>Improve our</b> <a href="/wiki/Category:Stub-Class_Globalization_articles" title="Category:Stub-Class Globalization articles">Stub-Class Globalization articles</a> (100).</li>\n<li><b><i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:As_of" title="Wikipedia:As of">Update</a></i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> <a href="/wiki/Globalization_Index" class="mw-redirect" title="Globalization Index">Globalization Index</a></li>\n<li><b><i>Other</i>\xe2\x80\x89:</b> Assess and recommend resources (online and print\xe2\x80\x93for the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization/Resources" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization/Resources">resources</a> page), add Globalization navigation template <code>{{<a href="/wiki/Template:Globalization" title="Template:Globalization">Globalization</a>}}</code> at bottom of key articles; post assessment criteria as per the table at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Globalization/Assessment#Importance_scale" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization/Assessment">Wikipedia:WikiProject Globalization/Assessment#Importance scale</a>, add <b>{{Portal|Globalization}}</b> to related articles (typically in See also sections)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page">Purge this page\'s server cache.</span></a></span></p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:both; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #aaaaaa; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #08088A; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Globalization/Key_topics&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Key_topics">Key topics</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div role="navigation" class="navbox" aria-labelledby="Globalization" style="padding:3px">\n<table class="nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner" style="border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit">\n<tr>\n<th scope="col" class="navbox-title" colspan="2">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Globalization" title="Template:Globalization"><abbr title="View this template" style=";;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-b